%3Cp%3EHow%20has%20the%20appeal%20to%20custom%20and%20culture%20impacted%20the%20judiciary%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20to%20have%20had%20a%20direct%20impact%20as%20the%20judiciary%20too%20has%20started%20appealing%20to%20culture%20and%20customs%20to%20justify%20imposing%20restrictions%20on%20fundamental%20rights%20or%20writing%20them%20out%20of%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENothing%20illustrates%20this%20better%20than%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2022%2F36593%2F36593_2022_1_1501_47792_Judgement_17-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20Justice%20P.S.%20Narasimha%20in%20the%20marriage%20equality%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fmarriage-equality-judgment-an-explainer%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0case%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20involved%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F15480%2F1%2Fspecial_marriage_act.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20begins%20by%20saying%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMarriage%20is%20a%20social%20institution%20and%20the%20status%20of%20the%20right%20to%20marry%3A%20There%20cannot%20be%20any%20quarrel%2C%20in%20my%20opinion%2C%20that%20marriage%20is%20a%20social%20institution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20questions%20arise%20from%20this%20bald%20statement.%20In%20what%20sense%20of%20the%20word%20is%20marriage%20a%20social%20institution%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20might%20answer%20this%20question%20by%20saying%20that%20its%20breakdown%20has%20consequences%20for%20the%20parties%20to%20the%20marriage%20and%20the%20children%20of%20the%20marriage.%20These%20are%20issues%20that%20can%20be%20addressed%20by%20secular%20law%2C%20not%20religious%20codes%2C%20as%20has%20been%20done%20for%20the%20Hindu%20law%20of%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20learned%20judge%20then%20proceeds%20to%20say%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20our%20country%2C%20it%20%5Bmarriage%5D%20is%20conditioned%20by%20culture%2C%20religion%2C%20customs%20and%20usages.%C2%A0It%20is%20a%20sacrament%20in%20some%20communities%20and%20a%20contract%20in%20some%20other.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20logical%20connection%20between%20these%20two%20statements.%20Even%20if%20marriage%20was%20not%20governed%20by%20sacrament%20or%20contract%2C%20it%20would%20still%20have%20social%20consequences%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20homelessness%20of%20women%20or%20the%20abandonment%20of%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20still%20be%20a%20social%20institution%20in%20which%20the%20society%20has%20a%20stake%20and%20the%20State%20has%20a%20legitimate%20interest%20in%20intervening%20to%20prevent%20the%20adverse%20consequences%20of%20a%20breakdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20whether%20marriage%20is%20a%20sacrament%20or%20a%20contract%20has%20consequences%20only%20for%20the%20form%20in%20which%20the%20marriage%20is%20solemnised.%20Some%20people%20choose%20to%20solemnise%20marriage%20in%20a%20secular%20form%2C%20some%20in%20a%20religious%20form%20and%20some%20in%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20let%20us%20look%20at%20the%20issue%20of%20marriage%20as%20a%20contract.%20What%20is%20being%20referred%20to%20here%20is%20the%C2%A0nikah%C2%A0at%20the%20time%20of%20a%20Muslim%20marriage%20where%20the%20man%20and%20the%20woman%20agree%20to%20wed%20each%20other.%20That%20is%20the%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20should%20not%20be%20something%20special%20to%20Muslim%20marriages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20it%20being%20suggested%20that%20a%20Hindu%20marriage%20does%20not%20require%20the%20two%20parties%20to%20consent%20to%20the%20marriage%20simply%20because%20it%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Csacrament%E2%80%9D%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20be%20a%20preposterous%20proposition%20to%20make%20and%20hence%20one%20must%20presume%20that%20a%20Hindu%20marriage%20involving%20a%C2%A0%3Cem%3Esaptapadi%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0also%20required%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20two%20parties%20to%20the%20marriage.%20This%20argument%20applies%20equally%20to%20a%20Parsi%20marriage%20or%20a%20Christian%20marriage%20or%20a%20secular%20marriage%20under%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20then%20goes%20on%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CState%20regulation%20in%20the%20form%20of%20codification%20has%20often%20reflected%20the%20customary%20and%20religious%20moorings%20of%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20exercise%20to%20identify%20the%20purpose%20of%20marriage%20or%20to%20find%20its%20%E2%80%98true%E2%80%99%20character%20is%20a%20pursuit%20that%20is%20as%20diverse%20and%20mystic%20as%20the%20purpose%20of%20human%20existence%3B%20and%20therefore%2C%20is%20not%20suited%20for%20judicial%20navigation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20complete%20cop-out.%20To%20say%20that%20the%20law%20in%20any%20circumstances%20cannot%20decide%20the%20content%20of%20marriage%20is%20to%20avoid%20a%20decision%20on%20the%20subject.%20I%20have%20said%20elsewhere%20that%20it%20is%20an%20agreement%2C%20hence%20a%20contract%20requiring%20informed%20consent%20between%20two%20people%20to%20share%20their%20lives%2C%20their%20hopes%20and%20aspirations%20with%20each%20other%2C%20their%20joys%20and%20their%20tragedies%2C%20to%20have%20sexual%20intercourse%20with%20each%20other%2C%20the%20exclusion%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthere-may-be-a-silver-lining-in-the-supreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgement%5C%22%3EThere%20May%20Be%20a%20Silver%20Lining%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Marriage%20Equality%20Judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20choice%20of%20partner%2C%20the%20State%20has%20no%20legitimate%20interest.%20What%20the%20State%20does%20have%20a%20legitimate%20interest%20in%20is%20the%20distribution%20of%20assets%20and%20custody%20of%20children%20upon%20the%20breakdown%20of%20a%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20then%20goes%20on%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20that%20does%20not%20render%20the%20institution%20meaningless%20or%20abstract%20for%20those%20who%20in%20their%20own%20way%20understand%20and%20practice%20it.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0Indeed%20people%20do%20have%20their%20own%20understanding%20of%20what%20marriage%20is%20and%20it%20is%20far%20from%20being%20meaningless%20or%20abstract.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20the%20judge%20in%20question%20it%20does%20render%20the%20institution%20abstract%20since%20%E2%80%9Cto%20identify%20the%20purpose%20of%20marriage%20or%20to%20find%20its%20true%20character%20that%20is%20as%20diverse%20and%20mystic%20as%20the%20purpose%20of%20human%20existence%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20judge%20here%20who%20has%20abandoned%20his%20judicial%20robe%20and%20put%20on%20that%20of%20a%20mystic.%20One%20wonders%20why%20it%20is%20so%20important%20to%20give%20marriage%20such%20an%20exalted%20social%20status%20if%20one%20is%20not%20able%20to%20define%20it.%20Surely%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20a%20social%20institution%20and%20a%20mystic%20one%20at%20the%20same%20time!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20then%20told%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20rules%20governing%20marriage%20and%20family%2C%20were%20largely%20customary%2C%20often%20rooted%20in%20religious%20practice.%20This%20exercise%20of%20codification%2C%20not%20always%20accurate%20and%20many%20a%20time%20exclusionary%2C%20was%20the%20product%20of%20the%20colonial%20desire%20to%20mould%20and%20reimagine%20our%20social%20institutions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20here%20that%20we%20can%20identify%20in%20the%20judgment%20the%20underlying%20major%20premise%20(unspoken).%20Marriages%20are%20largely%20governed%20by%20religion%2C%20(and%20should%20continue%20to%20be)%20save%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccolonial%20desire%20to%20remould%20and%20reimagine%20our%20social%20institutions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20amnesia%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20social%20reformers%20of%20Indian%20origin%20campaigned%20for%20the%20abolition%20of%C2%A0sati%2C%20for%20widow%20remarriage%2C%20for%20the%20right%20of%20woman%20to%20education%2C%20and%20for%20gender%20equality%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20inheritance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20call%20it%20%E2%80%9Ccolonial%20desire%E2%80%9D%20is%20ahistorical.%20It%20also%20echoes%20the%20narrative%20of%20the%20ruling%20party%20that%20they%20are%20decolonising%20laws%20passed%20by%20the%20British%20%E2%80%93%20the%20language%20here%20is%20similar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20subsequent%20mention%20of%20much-needed%20social%20reform%20does%20not%20make%20a%20difference%20to%20the%20underlying%20issue%20that%20marriage%20is%20a%20religious%20not%20a%20social%20institution%20governed%20by%20ancient%20custom%20which%20predates%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%20One%20must%20not%20forget%20the%20fact%20that%20custom%2C%20in%20order%20to%20be%20law%2C%20must%20be%20shown%20to%20exist%20since%20%E2%80%9Ctime%20immemorial%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20then%20told%2C%20%E2%80%9CEven%20when%20our%20own%20constitutional%20State%20attempted%20codification%20and%20reform%2C%20it%20left%20room%20for%20customary%20practices%20to%20co-exist%2C%20sometimes%20providing%20legislative%20heft%20to%20such%20customary%20practices.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDifferent%20marriage%20laws%20are%20then%20cited%20to%20substantiate%20this.%20A%20glance%20at%20each%20of%20these%20indicates%20that%20they%20all%20relate%20to%20the%C2%A0form%20in%20which%20marriages%20may%20be%20solemnised%2C%20including%20diverse%20religious%20forms%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20failure%20to%20recognise%20that%20none%20of%20these%20laws%20address%20the%20substance%20of%20what%20is%20a%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bouquet%20of%20statutes%20offers%20a%20choice%20to%20parties%20to%20a%20marriage%20in%20what%20manner%20they%20wish%20to%20solemnise%20a%20marriage%20but%20what%20they%20have%20in%20common%20is%20the%20fact%20of%20a%20marriage%20by%20consent%20of%20the%20parties%2C%20not%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmystic%E2%80%9D%20pursuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20form%20in%20which%20a%20marriage%20is%20solemnised%20cannot%20take%20away%20from%20the%20essential%20substance%20of%20a%20marriage%2C%20be%20it%20heterosexual%20or%20queer.%20There%20is%20an%20utter%20confusion%20between%20understanding%20the%20substance%20of%20the%20marriage%20and%20the%20form%20in%20which%20it%20is%20solemnised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20true%20that%20most%20marriage%20laws%20do%20have%20two%20substantive%20qualifications%2C%20one%20of%20age%20and%20the%20second%20the%20exclusion%20of%20prohibited%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20so%20that%20the%20State%20can%20have%20a%20legitimate%20interest%20in%20ensuring%20that%20those%20who%20consent%20to%20a%20marriage%20are%20in%20a%20position%20to%20give%20informed%20consent%20and%20so%20far%20as%20the%20prohibited%20degrees%20are%20concerned%2C%20this%20is%20for%20reasons%20of%20maintaining%20the%20health%20of%20the%20community%20and%20prevent%20inbreeding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20be%20said%20to%20be%20reasonable%20restrictions%20on%20the%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20constitutional%20or%20statutory.%20What%20is%20more%2C%20the%20restriction%20on%20prohibited%20degrees%20can%20be%20waived%20by%20custom.%20Hence%2C%20custom%2C%20far%20from%20restricting%20the%20choice%20of%20partner%2C%20enhances%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%20for%20the%20final%20punch%2C%20the%20underlying%20premise%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20my%20considered%20opinion%2C%20the%20institutional%20space%20of%20marriage%20is%20conditioned%20and%20occupied%20synchronously%20by%20legislative%20interventions%2C%20customary%20practices%20and%20religious%20beliefs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20extant%20legislative%20accommodation%20of%20customary%20and%20religious%20practices%20is%20not%20gratuitous%20and%20is%20to%20some%20extent%20conditioned%20by%20the%20right%20to%20religion%20and%20the%20right%20to%20culture%2C%20constitutionally%20sanctified%20in%20Articles%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-25-freedom-of-conscience-and-free-profession-practice-and-propagation-of-religion%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A025%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20Article%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-29-protection-of-interests-of-minorities%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A029%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20synchronously%20occupied%20institutional%20space%20of%20marriage%20is%20a%20product%20of%20our%20social%20and%20constitutional%20realities%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20in%20my%20opinion%2C%20comparative%20judicial%20perspectives%20offer%20little%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGiven%20this%20nature%20of%20marriage%20as%20an%20institution%2C%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20a%20spouse%20and%20the%20right%20of%20a%20consenting%20couple%20to%20be%20recognised%20within%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%2C%20cannot%20but%20be%20said%20to%20be%20restricted.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20there%20we%20have%20it%2C%20the%20right%20to%20marry%20is%20not%20a%20fundamental%20right%20but%20wait%20a%20minute%2C%20even%20if%20it%20was%2C%20it%20can%20be%20restricted%20by%20culture%20and%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20hierarchy%20of%20norms%2C%20this%20represents%20a%20complete%20surrender%20of%20our%20constitutional%20freedoms%20and%20rights%20to%20%E2%80%9Cculture%E2%80%9D%2C%20howsoever%20defined%2C%20with%20which%20the%20courts%20cannot%20interfere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20logical%20fallacies%20and%20contradictions%20in%20this%20judgment%20are%20immense.%20Understating%20statutes%20is%20weak%2C%20with%20an%20inability%20to%20distinguish%20between%20formal%20validity%20and%20substantive%20validity%20of%20a%20marriage%2C%20an%20understanding%20of%20what%20are%20called%20%E2%80%9Cpersonal%20laws%E2%80%9D%20is%20absent%20(notice%20that%20the%20words%20are%20not%20mentioned%20here).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20indeed%20there%20is%20no%20fundamental%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20what%20is%20there%20to%20prevent%20the%20State%20from%20telling%20us%20who%20to%20marry%20and%20who%20not%20to%20marry%2C%20or%20from%20saying%20Bharatiya%20culture%20will%20determine%20that%20question%20as%20well%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20points%20out%2C%20%E2%80%9CEven%20today%2C%20much%20of%20the%20Mohammedan%20law%20of%20marriage%20is%20governed%20by%20religious%20texts%20and%20customs%20and%20there%20is%20hardly%20any%20State%20intervention.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20not%20talking%20about%20the%20role%20of%20the%20State%20here%20but%20that%20of%20the%20judiciary%20in%20sitting%20in%20judgments%20over%20statutory%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20forgot%20to%20mention%20that%20in%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2016%2F6716%2F6716_2016_Judgement_22-Aug-2017.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3EShayara%20Bano%20versus%20Union%20of%20India%20and%20others%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20struck%20done%20the%20customary%20practice%20of%20triple%20talaq%20at%20the%20invitation%20of%20a%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)-led%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftriple-talaq-why-just-muslims-lets-criminalise-the-abandonment-of-all-wives%5C%22%3ETriple%20Talaq%3A%20Why%20Just%20Muslims%2C%20Let%E2%80%99s%20Criminalise%20the%20Abandonment%20of%20All%20Wives%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20judge%20states%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20claim%20of%20the%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20de%20hors%20the%20existing%20statutory%20framework%2C%20is%20nothing%20but%20a%20claim%20to%20create%20a%20legally%20and%20socially%20enforceable%20status.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMay%20we%20have%20a%20legal%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cstatus%E2%80%9D%3F%20Being%20unmarried%20is%20also%20a%20status%2C%20not%20created%20by%20law%2C%20so%20what%20is%20the%20relevance%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20marriage%20is%20a%20status%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20is%20the%20question%20of%20marriage%20laws%20not%20being%20standalone%20laws.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20interact%20in%20multifarious%20ways%20with%20succession%2C%20inheritance%20and%20adoption%20laws%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20all%20these%20already%20have%20existing%20statutory%20frameworks.%20So%20far%20as%20inheritance%20is%20concerned%2C%20almost%20all%20personal%20laws%20permit%20the%20making%20of%20a%20will%20and%20the%20disposing%20of%20property%20to%20a%20greater%20or%20lesser%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20was%20specifically%20amended%20to%20ensure%20that%20if%20two%20Hindus%20marry%20under%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%20they%20do%20not%20have%20to%20be%20governed%20by%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2385%2F1%2Fa1925-39.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Indian%20Succession%20Act%2C%201925%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0but%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20governed%20by%20their%20personal%20laws.%20Incidentally%2C%20this%20exception%20was%20made%20for%20Hindus%20alone%20and%20no%20other%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20concluded%20there%20is%20no%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20the%20judge%20concludes%20there%20is%20no%20right%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cunion%20or%20an%20abiding%20cohabitational%20relationship%E2%80%9D.%20Perhaps%20he%20overlooked%20the%20definition%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdomestic%20relationship%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F15436%2F1%2Fprotection_of_women_from_domestic_violence_act%252C_2005.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Protection%20of%20Woman%20from%20Domestic%20Violence%20Act%2C%202005%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0which%20recognises%20relationships%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20nature%20of%20marriage%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20opines%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20insufficient%20if%20persons%20have%20the%20ability%20and%20freedom%20to%20form%20relationships%20unregulated%20by%20the%20State%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0He%20goes%20on%20to%20state%20that%20there%20is%20no%20right%20to%20%E2%80%9Crecognition%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20relationship%20by%20the%20State.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20forgets%20that%20in%20the%C2%A0Shayara%20Bano%C2%A0case%2C%20the%20argument%20made%20was%20the%20act%20of%20recognition%20of%20triple%20talaq%20was%20an%20act%20of%20the%20State%20and%20it%20should%20be%20derecognised%20by%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20my%20considered%20opinion%2C%20it%20is%20in%20positively%20mandating%20the%C2%A0State%20to%20grant%20recognition%20or%20legal%20status%20to%20%E2%80%98unions%E2%80%99%20from%20which%20benefits%20will%20flow%2C%20that%20the%20doctrine%20of%20separation%20of%20powers%20is%20violated.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWas%20the%20doctrine%20of%20separation%20of%20powers%20violated%20when%20the%20court%20declared%20triple%20talaq%20unconstitutional%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20P.S.%20Narasimha%20continues%2C%20referring%20to%20his%20disagreement%20with%20the%20judgment%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20%E2%80%9CMoreover%2C%20the%20right%20to%20a%20union%20cannot%20be%20located%20in%20Article%2025%C2%A0of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEmphasis%20is%20placed%20on%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98freedom%20of%20conscience%E2%80%99%20because%20that%20would%20situate%20in%20this%20freedom%20of%20conscience%2C%20the%20right%20not%20only%20to%20judge%20the%20moral%20quality%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20action%20but%20also%20to%20act%20upon%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20that%20were%20permissible%20under%20Article%2025%2C%20then%20the%20textual%20enumeration%20of%20freedoms%20in%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-19-protection-of-certain-rights-regarding-freedom-of-speech-etc%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Article%2019%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0becomes%20redundant%20since%20these%20freedoms%20can%20be%20claimed%20to%20be%20actions%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20moral%20judgment.%20I%20find%20it%20difficult%20to%20agree%20with%20such%20a%20reading%20of%20Article%2025.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20fallacies%20here.%20Article%2025%20explicitly%20allows%20us%20to%20judge%20the%20moral%20quality%20of%20our%20actions%20and%20to%20act%20on%20them%20so%20long%20as%20we%20do%20not%20harm%20public%20order%2C%20morality%2C%20health%20and%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENowhere%20does%20the%20judge%20state%20that%20non-heterosexual%20relationships%20are%20immoral.%20Moreover%2C%20way%20back%20in%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1766147%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Maneka%20Gandhi%20vs%20Union%20Of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%C2%A0the%20court%20pointed%20out%20that%20rights%20overlap%20with%20each%20other%20and%20create%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20triangle%E2%80%9D.%20Hence%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20is%20an%20overlap%20in%20the%20content%20of%20the%20right%20is%20of%20no%20consequence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20concludes%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20the%20reasons%20stated%20above%20the%20Petitions%20are%20dismissed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20shows%20that%2C%20mirroring%20the%20Executive%2C%20our%20courts%20have%20set%20up%20a%20norm%20above%20the%20norm%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20i.e.%2C%20culture%2C%20and%20will%20not%20enforce%20the%20text%20of%20the%20Constitution%20when%20it%20conflicts%20with%20the%20culture%2C%20howsoever%20defined.%20It%20is%20indeed%20the%20repudiation%20of%20the%20judicial%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20community%20needs%20to%20be%20vigilant%20to%20prevent%20this%20failing%20court%20since%20the%20future%20of%20the%20rights%20of%20citizens%20seems%20to%20be%20in%20jeopardy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20marriage%20equality%20judgment%20is%20the%20only%20judgment%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20besides%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F925631%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0one%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20held%20that%20Hinduism%20is%20a%20way%20of%20life%20and%20not%20religion%20alone%20which%20legitimises%20culture%20as%20the%20measure%20of%20whether%20a%20restriction%20on%20a%20right%20was%20reasonable%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20note%20that%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-13-laws-inconsistent-with-or-in-derogation-of-the-fundamental-rights%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Article%2013%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20declares%20all%20laws%20that%20violate%20fundamental%20rights%20void%2C%20defines%20law%20to%20include%20%E2%80%9Ccustom%E2%80%9D%20but%20it%20does%20not%20include%20%E2%80%98culture%E2%80%99%20as%20law.%20Yet%20today%20we%20have%20a%20judgment%20that%20clearly%20permits%20culture%20to%20trump%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20cultural%20test%20of%20%E2%80%9Creasonableness%E2%80%9D%20can%20be%20used%20to%20uphold%20governmental%20action%2C%20why%20can%20it%20not%20be%20used%20to%20interpret%20the%20Constitution%20itself%20or%20the%20validity%20of%20a%20constitutional%20amendment%20for%20that%20matter%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F257876%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKeshavananda%20Bharati%20versus%20State%20of%20Kerala%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20decided%20in%201973%2C%20held%20that%20the%20basic%20features%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20such%20as%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20secularism%2C%20democracy%20and%20federalism%2C%20could%20not%20be%20amended%20even%20by%20a%20Constitutional%20amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20today%20we%20see%20the%20same%20result%20as%20we%20would%20by%20an%20amendment%20by%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20norm%20higher%20than%20and%20inconsistent%20with%20the%20values%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20new%20set%20of%20practices%20has%20replaced%20constitutionalism%20and%20legality%20and%20has%20been%20elevated%20to%20the%20level%20above%20the%20Constitution%20with%20reference%20to%20which%20the%20Constitution%20and%20its%20basic%20features%20are%20to%20be%20interpreted.%20Rights%2C%20as%20we%20know%20them%2C%20are%20replaced%20by%20duties%2C%20negating%20the%20entire%20chapter%20on%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20fundamental%20duties%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fconstitution-day-fundamental-duties-should-be-the-first-priority-of-citizens-says-pm-modi%2Farticleshow%2F95782187.cms%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0now%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0take%20precedence%20over%20our%20fundamental%20rights.%20We%20must%20all%20do%20our%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fgovernor-tathagata-roy-most-controversial-statements-5594182%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekartavya%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20without%20any%20expectation%20of%20freedom.%20A%20new%20language%20of%20politics%20and%20consequentially%20law%20has%20been%20invented%20in%20place%20of%20constitutionalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20told%20that%20there%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fhindu-dharma-has-taken-over-constitutional-values-says-indira-jaising-at-the-sixth-neelabh-mishra-lecture%2F%5C%22%3Eintrinsic%20dharma%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20people%20of%20India%20which%20is%20ancient%20and%20predates%20the%20Constitution.%20Once%20a%20norm%20above%20the%20Constitution%20is%20created%2C%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20see%20why%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20amend%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20why%20I%20say%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthere-is-no-lack-of-judicial-power-in-india-just-a-refusal-to-act-on-it%5C%22%3Ethat%202023%20has%20been%20the%20year%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Esurajmukhi%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0court.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIndira%20Jaising%20is%20a%20noted%20human%20rights%20lawyer%20and%20a%20senior%20advocate%20at%20