pakistan%2Farticleshow%2F106588595.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Big%20Day%20For%20India's%20Sun%20Mission%2C%20Aditya-L1%20To%20Enter%20Final%20Orbit%20Today%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fisros-aditya-l1-satellite-has-a-date-with-the-sun-4802774%5C%22%3EAditya-L1%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India's%20first%20mission%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faditya-l1-of-indias-sun-mission-takes-a-selfie-clicks-images-of-earth-and-moon-isro-4367344%5C%22%3Estudy%20the%20sun%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20set%20to%20reach%20its%20final%20destination%20orbit%20on%20Saturday%2C%20over%20four%20months%20after%20it%20began%20its%20ambitious%20journey%20from%20ISRO's%20Sriharikota%20launchpad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBuilt%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%20400%20crore%2C%20the%20nearly%201%2C500%20kg%20satellite%20will%20function%20as%20the%20first%20space-based%20Indian%20observatory%20to%20study%20the%20sun%20nearly%201.5%20million%20kilometres%20from%20the%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fisro-shares-first-light-of-sun-captured-by-aditya-l1-4554835%5C%22%3Esatellite%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20placed%20in%20a%20halo%20orbit%20around%20Lagrange%20point%201%20(L1)%20at%20around%204%20pm.%20The%20final%20insertion%20point%20was%20chosen%20for%20its%20advantageous%20position%20which%20remains%20unhindered%20by%20eclipses%20and%20can%20be%20used%20to%20view%20the%20Sun%20continuously.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20manoeuvre%20(at%20around%204%20pm%20on%20Saturday)%20will%20bind%20the%20Aditya-L1%20to%20a%20halo%20orbit%20around%20L1.%20If%20we%20don't%20do%20this%2C%20there%20is%20a%20possibility%20that%20it%20will%20continue%20its%20journey%2C%20maybe%20towards%20the%20Sun%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20ISRO%20official%20told%20news%20agency%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20space%20observatory%20will%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20changing%20space%20weather%20and%20warn%20scientists%20about%20unfavourable%20changes%20including%20solar%20storms%20and%20flares%20that%20may%20impact%20the%20working%20of%20satellites.%20A%20solar%20storm%20is%20a%20large-scale%20magnetic%20eruption%20on%20the%20Sun%2C%20which%20can%20effect%20the%20entire%20solar%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20Aditya-L1%20will%20look%20at%20Sun%20continuously%2C%20it%20can%20warn%20us%20of%20imminent%20solar%20electro-magnetic%20effects%20on%20Earth%20and%20protect%20our%20satellites%2C%20and%20other%20power%20electrical%20and%20communications%20networks%20from%20getting%20disrupted.%20This%20will%20help%20continue%20normal%20operations%20by%20operating%20them%20in%20safe%20modes%2C%20till%20the%20solar%20storm%20passes%20by%2C%26quot%3B%20ISRO%20Chairman%20S%20Somanath%20had%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Somnath%20said%20that%20India%20has%20assets%20worth%20over%20%E2%82%B9%2050%2C000%20crores%20in%20space%20including%20over%2050%20operational%20satellites%20that%20need%20to%20be%20protected%20against%20the%20wrath%20of%20the%20Sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Aditya-L1%20satellite%2C%20carrying%20seven%20payloads%2C%20will%20also%20conduct%20scientific%20experiments%20to%20better%20understand%20the%20photosphere%2C%20chromosphere%20and%20the%20outermost%20layers%20of%20the%20Sun%20(the%20corona)%20using%20electromagnetic%2C%20particle%20and%20magnetic%20field%20detectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20less-studied%20solar%20weather%2C%20the%20satellite%20will%20gain%20crucial%20information%20about%20pre-flare%20and%20flare%20activities%20and%20the%20dynamics%20of%20space%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20ISRO%2C%20these%20are%20the%20major%20scientific%20objectives%20of%20Aditya-L1%20mission%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EStudy%20solar%20upper%20atmospheric%20(chromosphere%20and%20corona)%20