%20their%20consideration%20and%20will%20hear%20oral%20arguments%20on%20February%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20anyone's%20guess%20as%20to%20the%20justices'%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20will%20be%20thinking%20about%20the%20ramifications%20of%20this%20decision%20in%20many%20respects%2C%20including%20the%20ramifications%20for%20the%20Court%20itself%20and%20the%20ramifications%20for%20the%20country%20more%20broadly%2C%26quot%3B%20Carolyn%20Shapiro%2C%20founder%20of%20Chicago-Kent's%20Institute%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20experts%20who%20spoke%20with%20Business%20Insider%20offer%20varied%20perspectives%20on%20how%20the%20justices%20%E2%80%94%20three%20appointed%20under%20the%20Trump%20administration%20%E2%80%94%20could%20determine%20the%20fate%20of%20Trump's%20eligibility%20on%20the%20ballot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20McMahon%2C%20a%20political%20science%20professor%20at%20Trinity%20College%20who%20is%20currently%20writing%20a%20book%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20uncertainty%20around%20how%20the%20justices%20will%20rule%20no%20matter%20how%20partisan%20the%20Court%20is%20accused%20of%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20to%20conservative%20former%20federal%20judge%20J.%20Michael%20Luttig%2C%20who%20told%20MSNBC%20in%20December%20of%20last%20year%20that%20the%20Colorado%20case%20is%20not%20a%20partisan%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20be%20crystal%20clear%20to%20the%20American%20public%20that%20it's%20the%20Constitution%20of%20the%20United%20States%20that's%20disqualifying%20the%20former%20president%20from%20higher%20office%2C%20if%20he%20is%20to%20be%20disqualified%2C%26quot%3B%20Luttig%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%20It's%20not%20the%20Democrats.%20It's%20not%20the%20anti-Trumpers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShapiro%20similarly%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20certainty%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20very%2C%20very%20strong%20arguments%2C%20including%20originalists%20arguments%2C%20that%20he%20is%20disqualified%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20a%20legal%20theory%20in%20which%20the%20Consitution%20is%20interpreted%20as%20it%20was%20intended%20when%20it%20was%20written.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20arguments%20that%20he%20is%20not%20disqualified%20are%20not%20entirely%20frivolous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20around%20Trump's%20ineligibility%20revolves%20around%20a%20section%20of%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20which%20states%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BNo%20person%20shall%20be%20a%20Senator%20or%20Representative%20in%20Congress%2C%20or%20elector%20of%20President%20and%20Vice-President%2C%20or%20hold%20any%20office%2C%20civil%20or%20military%2C%20under%20the%20United%20States%2C%20or%20under%20any%20State%2C%20who%2C%20having%20previously%20taken%20an%20oath%2C%20as%20a%20member%20of%20Congress%2C%20or%20as%20an%20officer%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20or%20as%20a%20member%20of%20any%20State%20legislature%2C%20or%20as%20an%20executive%20or%20judicial%20officer%20of%20any%20State%2C%20to%20support%20the%20Constitution%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20shall%20have%20engaged%20in%20insurrection%20or%20rebellion%20against%20the%20same%2C%20or%20given%20aid%20or%20comfort%20to%20the%20enemies%20thereof.%20But%20Congress%20may%20by%20a%20vote%20of%20two-thirds%20of%20each%20House%2C%20remove%20such%20disability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20lawyers%20who%20filed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frepublicans-gop-voters-lawsuit-disqualifying-trump-colorado-ballot-supreme-court-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EColorado%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20seeking%20to%20ban%20Trump%20from%20the%20primary%20ballot%20have%20argued%20that%20the%20law%20applies%20to%20Trump%20due%20to%20his%20actions%20on%20January%206%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20the%20case%20on%20the%20facts%20of%20the%20law%20is%20strong%2C%26quot%3B%20Donald%20Sherman%2C%20one%20of%20the%20lead%20attorneys%20behind%20the%20Colorado%20lawsuit%2C%20previously%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWe%20also%20think%20that%20the%20case%20on%20the%20facts%20of%20the%20law%20is%20an%20originalist%20case%20for%20Donald%20Trump's%20disqualification.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20arguments%20in%20Trump's%20favor%20is%20that%20the%20presidency%20should%20not%20be%20treated%20the%20same%20way%20as%20any%20other%20office%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Shapiro%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20judge%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.courts.state.co.us%2Fuserfiles%2Ffile%2FCourt_Probation%2F02nd_Judicial_District%2FDenver_District_Court%2F11_17_2023%2520Final%2520Order.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower%20Colorado%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20initially%20ruled%20that%20Trump%20is%20an%20insurrectionist%3B%20however%2C%20the%20original%20drafters%20of%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20intend%20to%20include%20the%20President%20as%20'%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-2024-campaign-january-6-insurrection-run-for-president-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20officer%20of%20the%20United%20States%3C%2Fa%3E.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%20ultimately%20overruled%20that%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaine's%20secretary%20of%20state%20has%20said%20Trump%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-ineligible-maines-primary-ballot-secretary-of-state-rules-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eineligible%20for%20the%20ballot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20other%20states%20have%20pending%20litigation.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20could%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20do%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%20could%20decide%20to%20keep%20Trump%20on%20the%20ballots%20or%20ban%20him%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Shapiro%20adds%20that%20there%20are%20also%20more%20limited%20ways%20the%20Court%20could%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Court%20could%20rule%20either%20very%20narrowly%20so%20as%20to%20not%20affect%20other%20types%20of%20elections.%20There%20are%20ways%20that%20they%20could%20rule%20that%20would%20limit%20this%20particular%20holding%20to%20the%20presidency%20or%20maybe%20the%20vice%20presidency%2C%20for%20example.%20There%20are%20also%20ways%20that%20they%20could%20issue%20a%20ruling%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20avoid%20deciding%20the%20merits%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeama%20Rahmani%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20and%20President%20of%20West%20Coast%20Trial%2C%20argued%20that%20the%20outcome%20is%20clear%3A%20Trump%20will%20remain%20on%20the%20ballot%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%20agreed%20to%20take%20this%20case%20less%20than%20a%20week%20after%20(Trump)%20filed%20an%20appeal%20and%20they%20fast-tracked%20the%20oral%20argument%20to%20February%208%20and%20have%20expedited%20briefing%20%E2%80%94%20I%20mean%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20an%20expert%20or%20read%20the%20tea%20leaves%20to%20know%20which%20way%20this%20is%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20Rahmani%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BTrump%20is%20going%20to%20win.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20conservative%20justices%20have%20an%20originalist%20interpretation%20of%20the%20amendment%2C%20there's%20no%20real%20precedent%20to%20determine%20how%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20was%20enforced%2C%20Rhamani%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20really%20never%20has%20been%20litigated%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20all%20know%20what%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20says%3A%20You%20engaged%20in%20insurrection%2C%20you%20can't%20hold%20public%20office.%20But%20how%20is%20it%20enforced%3F%20Who%20enforces%20it%3F%