passive%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Gibson%2C%20passive%20parents%20can%20be%20really%20fun%20to%20be%20around.%20The%20problem%20is%2C%20they%20are%20passive%20about%20actually%20parenting%20%E2%80%94%20anything%20that%20isn't%20easy%20and%20light%20sends%20them%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20step%20in%20if%20the%20other%20parent%20is%20being%20volatile%20or%20even%20abusive%2C%20and%20they%20kind%20of%20let%20the%20kid%20fend%20for%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20said.%20And%20because%20they're%20passive%20by%20nature%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20end%20up%20with%20partners%20who%20are%20more%20eruptive%20and%20self-absorbed%2C%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20they%20can%20encourage%20their%20child%20more%20than%20an%20emotionally%20absent%20parent%20does%2C%20they%20also%20fail%20to%20show%20up%20when%20their%20kid%20is%20anything%20but%20happy.%20Gibson%20shared%20some%20signs%20that%20you%20grew%20up%20with%20a%20passive%20parent%2C%20and%20how%20it%20might%20be%20impacting%20your%20life%20even%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Your%20parent%20felt%20more%20like%20a%20friend%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20a%20parent%20who%20yells%20or%20ignores%20you%2C%20the%20passive%20parent%20is%20more%20childlike%20themselves%20and%20can%20be%20really%20comforting%20to%20be%20around%2C%20Gibson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E'They're%20often%20the%20favorite%20parent%20because%20they%20have%20that%20kind%20of%20sympathy%20for%20being%20a%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20kind%20of%20floating%20along%20and%20they%20can%20be%20very%20sweet%20companions%20to%20children.%26quot%3B%20They're%20that%20parent%20you%20can%20have%20a%20blast%20playing%20with%20or%20who%20is%20always%20willing%20to%20go%20to%20a%20theme%20park.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20makes%20them%20emotionally%20immature%20is%20their%20inability%20to%20handle%20their%20emotions.%20Instead%20of%20screaming%2C%20however%2C%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsigns-symptoms-you-are-struggling-with-emotional-dysregulation-2023-9%3F_gl%3D1*qr6z0t*_ga*MTY5MDkzMTcwNy4xNjk5NTYwNTcz*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTcwNDQ3Njk5Ny4xMjcuMS4xNzA0NDc5MTM2LjMwLjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithdraw%20when%20there's%20any%20discomfort%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLike%20a%20kind%20of%20uncertain%20child%2C%20they%20might%20pull%20back%20or%20they%20might%20hesitate%2C%20might%20defer%20to%20the%20more%20dominant%20parent%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that%20can%20be%20very%20damaging%20by%20default%20when%20you%20don't%20protect%20your%20child%20from%20a%20more%20forceful%20parent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20You%20avoid%20sharing%20any%20uncomfortable%20feelings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20passive%20parent%20might%20not%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-stop-argument-with-narcissist-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavoid%20conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20their%20partner%2C%20but%20may%20also%20dodge%20it%20with%20their%20own%20kid%2C%20Gibson%20said.%20The%20kid%20then%20learns%20that%20%26quot%3Bpositive%26quot%3B%20emotions%2C%20like%20joy%20and%20optimism%2C%20are%20good%20to%20show%2C%20but%20being%20angry%2C%20upset%2C%20or%20frustrated%20will%20make%20their%20cheerful%20parent%20pull%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20may%20feel%20like%20the%20parent%20is%20starting%20to%20withdraw%20and%20avoid%20the%20relationship%20with%20them%20because%20they%20think%20that%20they%20have%20made%20it%20too%20uncomfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20You%20might%20become%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-to-stop-being-a-people-pleaser-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epeople-pleaser%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20learning%20to%20cope%20by%20not%20being%20direct%20or%20asking%20for%20what%20you%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Gibson%2C%20the%20subconscious%20lesson%20you%20learn%20is%20%26quot%3BTry%20to%20put%20up%20with%20everything%20that%20happens%2C%20because%20that's%20what%20love%20is%2C%20and%20always%20be%20a%20nice%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20You%20feel%20stuck%20and%20helpless%20in%20your%20relationships%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20you've%20learned%20that%20sharing%20more%20complex%20feelings%20is%20inherently%20bad%2C%20you%20can%20end%20up%20in%20dissatisfying%20friendships%20and%20romantic%20partnerships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20lessons%20are%20a%20setup%20for%20unhappy%20relationships%20because%20there's%20no%20direct%20communication%2C%20there's%20no%20emotional%20sharing%2C%20and%20there's%20the%20sense%20that%20everything%20will%20get%20better%20if%20you%20just%20avoid%20dealing%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20makes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsigns-youre-in-a-healthy-relationship-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehealthy%20relationships%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20difficult%20because%20true%20intimacy%20requires%20embracing%20disagreement%20and%20being%20vulnerable%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20You%20let%20life%20happen%20to%20you%20instead%20of%20taking%20charge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPassive%20parents%20don't%20just%20teach%20you%20to%20avoid%20conflict%20in%20your%20relationships%2C%20but%20in%20other%20contexts%20as%20well%20including%20work%20and%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGibson%20said%20having%20a%20passive%20parent%20%26quot%3Bcan%20really%20have%20repercussions%20on%20your%20success%20in%20a%20career%20because%20that%20parent%20modeled%20a%20kind%20of%20passive%20orientation%20to%20life%20where%20you%20let%20things%20happen%20to%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20her%20experience%20with%20her%20clients%2C%20passive%20parents%20often%20don't%20understand%20their%20kids'%20ambitions%20or%20why%20they%20would%20put%20themselves%20through%20something%20challenging.%20To%20them%2C%20the%20best%20life%20involves%20letting%20things%20just%20fall%20into%20your%20lap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20you%20can%20feel%20discouraged%20from%20pursuing%20something%20grander%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-finland-happiest-place-never-visited-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoving%20to%20a%20new%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-jessica-mccabe-used-adhd-strengths-build-dream-career-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eswitching%20career%20paths%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20leaving%20a%20marriage%20%E2%80%94%20risks%20that%20could%20all%20lead%20to%20greater%20happiness%20(or%20at%20least%20a%20valuable%20learning%20experience).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Asking%20for%20more%20is%20a%20huge%20step%20for%20you%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20afraid%20of%20inconveniencing%20people%20and%20taking%20risks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-success-how-to-advocate-for-yourself-raise-promotion-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvocating%20for%20yourself%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20enormous%20step%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20believe%20that%20you%20deserve%20more%2C%20you%20may%20avoid%20voicing%20your%20opinion%2C%20asking%20for%20a%20promotion%2C%20or%20even%20just%20standing%20out%20at%20all%2C%20Gibson%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20might%20not%20grab%20that%20opportunity%20or%20you%20might%20back%20down%20from%20a%20work%20conflict%20that%20could%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20really%20improve%20things%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-raised-by-passive-parent-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704493742000%2C%22visual