20M.K.%20Stalin%E2%80%99s%20Cabinet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20perused%20the%20impugned%20judgment%20of%20the%20high%20court%20and%20concur%20with%20the%20view%20taken.%20No%20interference%20is%20called%20for%20under%20Article%20136%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Bench%20said%20dismissing%20the%20plea%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fsupreme-court-rejects-plea-remove-tamil-nadu-minister-v-senthil-balaji%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20136%20deals%20with%20the%20special%20leave%20to%20appeal%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20It%20means%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20authorised%20to%20grant%20in%20its%20discretion%20special%20leave%20to%20appeal%20from%20any%20judgement%20in%20any%20matter%20passed%20by%20any%20court%20or%20tribunal%20in%20the%20territory%20of%20India%20(except%20military%20tribunal%20and%20court-martial).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20also%20orally%20contended%20that%20a%20governor%20needs%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20chief%20minister%20to%20dismiss%20a%20minister%20and%20cannot%20act%20independently%20on%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBalaji%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20last%20year%20in%20a%20money%20laundering%20case.%20He%20was%20accused%20of%20being%20involved%20in%20a%20cash-for-jobs%20scam%20during%20his%20tenure%20as%20transport%20minister%20in%20the%20previous%20All%20India%20Anna%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam-led%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20between%202011%20and%202015.%20He%20later%20joined%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%20and%20became%20a%20minister%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20arrest%20in%20June%202023%2C%20Stalin%20withdrew%20all%20portfolios%20from%20Balaji%20but%20still%20retained%20him%20as%20a%20minister.%20An%20advocate%20R.L.%20Ravi%20moved%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%2C%20opposing%20Balaji%E2%80%99s%20continuance%20in%20the%20cabinet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fsupreme-court-remove-tamil-nadu-minister-senthil-balaji-state-cabinet-9096533%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20high%20court%20had%20said%20%E2%80%9Cministers%20without%20portfolios%20do%20not%20have%20any%20specific%20ministries%20nor%20they%20do%20have%20carved%20out%20responsibilities.%20The%20chief%20minister%20is%20an%20executive%20head.%20It%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20an%20executive%20head%20to%20assign%20ministerial%20responsibilities%20to%20an%20elected%20representative.%20However%2C%20if%20he%20feels%20that%20a%20particular%20elected%20representative%20cannot%20be%20assigned%20the%20responsibility%20of%20a%20minister%2C%20there%20cannot%20be%20a%20moral%20or%20constitutional%20basis%20to%20retain%20such%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20as%20a%20minister%20without%20a%20portfolio%2C%20which%20would%20be%20opposed%20to%20the%20ethos%2C%20good%20governance%2C%20and%20constitutional%20morality%20or%20integrity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704460258000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F04181601%2FSupreme-Court-and-Senthilbalaji.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-refuses-to-order-removal-of-senthil-balaji-from-tn-cabinet-upholds-madras-hc-verdict%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Madras%20high%20court%20had%20said%20that%20it%20is%20for%20the%20chief%20minister%20to%20take%20a%20call%20on%20the%20minister's%20continuance%20or%20removal%20despite%20him%20being%20in%20jail%20and%20stripped%20of%20a%20portfolio.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-refuses-to-order-removal-of-senthil-balaji-from-tn-cabinet-upholds-madras-hc-verdict%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tata