s%2C%20it%20was%20on%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20bestseller%20list%20for%2044%20weeks.%20Yet%20when%20we%20think%20of%20%3Cem%3EJaws%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20images%20from%20Steven%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%201975%20film%20adaptation%20are%20what%20come%20to%20mind%20%E2%80%93%20along%20with%20John%20Williams%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FE-sX2Y0W8l0%3Fsi%3D7H4TUsSRrImq_eh-%5C%22%3Eiconic%20theme%20music%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpielberg%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0073195%2F%5C%22%3EJaws%3C%2Fa%3E%20keeps%20the%20simple%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20and%20stunning%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20narrative%20architecture%20of%20Benchley%E2%80%99s%20novel%20intact.%20A%20shark%20terrorises%20a%20small%20beach%20community%20that%20depends%20on%20wealthy%20tourists%20for%20sustenance.%20Brody%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20police%2C%20keeps%20the%20beaches%20open%20due%20to%20political%20pressure%20from%20Mayor%20Vaughan%3B%20when%20more%20attacks%20occur%2C%20marine%20biologist%20Matt%20Hooper%20comes%20to%20help.%20Together%2C%20they%20contract%20wild%20shark%20hunter%20Quint%20to%20help%20them%20kill%20the%20great%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20tone%20of%20grand%20adventure%20that%20defines%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20film%20marks%20a%20major%20departure%20from%20the%20novel.%20In%20Benchley%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20more%20energy%20is%20directed%20towards%20exploring%20the%20minor%20social%20and%20political%20lives%20of%20its%20small-town%20denizens%20than%20in%20staging%20an%20epic%20showdown%20between%20man%20and%20beast%20%E2%80%93%20and%2C%20crucially%2C%20it%20differs%20radically%20from%20the%20film%20in%20its%20characterisation.%20In%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20world%2C%20the%20main%20characters%20are%20likeable%2C%20heroic%2C%20whereas%20in%20the%20novel%20they%E2%80%99re%20petty%2C%20broken%20and%20bitter%2C%20wading%20through%20the%20messes%20their%20personal%20lives%20have%20become.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20differences%20are%20not%20simply%20evidence%20of%20a%20young%20director%E2%80%99s%20desire%20to%20make%20the%20material%20his%20own.%20They%20map%20the%20changing%20consciousness%20of%20American%20popular%20culture%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20from%20a%20resolute%20focus%20on%20the%20violence%20simmering%20within%20United%20States%20society%20and%20policy%20(the%20civil%20rights%20movement%20and%20the%20Vietnam%20War)%20to%20an%20attempt%20to%20forget%20about%20these%20things%20through%20spectacular%2C%20anodyne%20entertainment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20know%2C%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20film%20reshaped%20Hollywood%2C%20virtually%20single-handedly%20inventing%20the%20%E2%80%9Cblockbuster%E2%80%9D%20and%20marking%20a%20significant%20shift%20away%20from%20the%20existentially%20charged%2C%20sometimes%20nihilistic%2C%20ever%20self-critical%20films%20of%20the%20previous%20decade%20or%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20two%20dominant%20themes%20situating%20Benchley%E2%80%99s%20novel%20in%20a%20rich%20American%20literary%20tradition%20also%20underpin%20the%20film%3A%20its%20biting%20look%20at%20small-town%20politics%20and%20economics%2C%20and%20its%20reverent%20study%20of%20a%20wilderness%20awesome%20and%20sublime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98The%20shark%20material%20is%20brilliant%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20core%20is%20a%20swift%2C%20economically%20told%20tale%20of%20human%20versus%20beast%3A%20a%20classic%20American%20adventure%20in%20the%20vein%20of%20Jack%20London%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguin.com.au%2Fbooks%2Fwhite-fang-9780241652664%5C%22%3EWhite%20Fang%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Herman%20Melville%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguin.com.au%2Fbooks%2Fmoby--dick-9780451532282%5C%22%3EMoby-Dick%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBenchley%20punctuates%20this%20drama%20with%20a%20keen%20interrogation%20of%20the%20social%20dynamics%20of%20small%20American%20communities%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20economic%20pressures%20of%20capitalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20career%20journalist%2C%20Benchley%20is%20effective%20in%20describing%20actions%2C%20events%20and%20scenery%3A%20shark%20hunting%2C%20the%20ocean%2C%20Quint%E2%80%99s%20boat.%20The%20shark%20material%20is%20brilliant%20%E2%80%93%20the%20few%20times%20it%20cuts%20to%20the%20shark%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%20(recalling%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20redeployment%20of%20the%20creature%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%20from%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0046876%2F%5C%22%3ECreature%20from%20the%20Black%20Lagoon%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20the%20writing%20becomes%20electric%2C%20effortless.%20Benchley%20is%20at%20his%20best%20when%20describing%20the%20movements%20of%20the%20shark%20in%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20when%20Hooper%20is%20cage%20diving%2C%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20novel%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20head%20was%20only%20a%20few%20feet%20from%20the%20cage%20when%20the%20fish%20turned%20and%20began%20to%20pass%20before%20Hooper%E2%80%99s%20eyes%20%E2%80%93%20casually%2C%20as%20if%20in%20proud%20display%20of%20its%20incalculable%20mass%20and%20power.%20The%20snout%20passed%20first%2C%20then%20the%20jaw%2C%20slack%20and%20smiling%2C%20armed%20with%20row%20upon%20row%20of%20serrate%20triangles.%20And%20then%20the%20black%2C%20fathomless%20eye%2C%20seemingly%20riveted%20upon%20him.%20The%20gills%20rippled%20%E2%80%93%20bloodless%20wounds%20in%20the%20steely%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20material%20about%20people%20is%20less%20confident%20%E2%80%93%20the%20writing%20is%20uneven%20and%20trite%20in%20places%2C%20with%20moments%20between%20characters%20sometimes%20strained%20in%20order%20to%20generate%20the%20necessary%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20two%20subplots%20Spielberg%20and%20team%20wisely%20cut%20from%20the%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20involves%20a%20murky%20connection%20between%20Mayor%20Vaughn%20and%20the%20Mob%20that%20is%20partly%20responsible%20for%20his%20desire%20to%20keep%20the%20beaches%20open%2C%20despite%20Brody%E2%80%99s%20warnings.%20It%20seems%20both%20underdeveloped%20%E2%80%93%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20find%20out%20much%20about%20it%20%E2%80%93%20and%20strangely%20present%2C%20with%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20scenes%20involving%20the%20mayor%20gesturing%20towards%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%2C%20which%20probably%20would%20have%20been%20fatal%20to%20the%20film%2C%20involves%20an%20affair%20between%20Brody%E2%80%99s%20wife%20Ellen%20and%20Matt%20Hooper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECharacters%20%E2%80%98loathsome%20in%20places%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20great%20joys%20of%20the%20film%20is%20the%20developing%20friendship%20between%20Hooper%20and%20Brody%2C%20culminating%20in%20their%20delightful%20final%20exchange.%20After%20the%20shark%20is%20dead%20and%20they%20are%20kicking%20their%20way%20back%20to%20shore%2C%20Brody%20laughs%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20used%20to%20hate%20the%20water.%E2%80%9D%20Hooper%20replies%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20can%E2%80%99t%20imagine%20why%E2%80%9D.%20Both%20men%20are%20happy%20to%20have%20survived%2C%20and%20to%20have%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20novel%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20more%20or%20less%20hate%20at%20first%20sight%2C%20with%20Brody%20immediately%20resenting%20Hooper%20because%20he%20grew%20up%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csummer%20person%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20area.%20Brody%20is%20ashamed%20he%E2%80%99s%20not%20one%20of%20the%20wealthy%20summer%20people%2C%20and%20tries%20to%20hide%20this%20through%20a%20kind%20of%20pathetic%20machismo%2C%20which%20emerges%20most%20visibly%20in%20his%20competitiveness%20with%20Hooper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20obsession%20with%20summer%20people%20defines%20much%20of%20the%20dialogue%20between%20Brody%20and%20Ellen%2C%20with%20Brody%E2%80%99s%20resentment%20of%20the%20summer%20people%E2%80%99s%20nonchalant%20and%20emasculating%20wealth%20matched%20by%20Ellen%E2%80%99s%20resentment%20of%20the%20fact%20she%20used%20to%20be%20a%20summer%20person%20before%20she%20married%20this%20oaf%20of%20a%20police%20chief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F565548%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231213-23-ko2crz.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D1000%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F565548%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231213-23-ko2crz.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D237%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22273%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F565548%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231213-23-ko2crz.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D880%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F565548%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231213-23-ko2crz.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D880%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F565548%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231213-23-ko2crz.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D880%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F565548%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231213-23-ko2crz.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D1106%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F565548%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231213-23-ko2crz.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D1106%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F565548%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231213-23-ko2crz.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D1106%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20characters%20in%20the%20novel%20are%20thus%20thoroughly%20unappealing%20%E2%80%93%20even%20loathsome%20in%20places.%20Spielberg%20famously%20stated%20the%20shark%20was%20his%20favourite%20character%20in%20the%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20film%E2%80%99s%20Brody%2C%20anchored%20by%20the%20effortless%20charisma%20of%20Roy%20Scheider%2C%20is%20a%20steadfast%2C%20stoic%20working%20man%20who%20loves%20his%20wife%20and%20children%20and%20isn%E2%80%99t%20ashamed%20to%20show%20it%20in%20a%20gentle%2C%20unassuming%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20novel%2C%20Brody%20is%20%E2%80%9Cjealous%20and%20injured%2C%20inadequate%20and%20outraged%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20chauvinistic%20beer-guzzling%20bully%2C%20an%20obsessive%20%E2%80%93%20and%20often%20self-loathing%20%E2%80%93%20jerk.%20One%20of%20our%20first%20forays%20into%20his%20consciousness%20makes%20this%20immediately%20apparent%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20during%20the%20summer%2C%20Brody%20would%20catch%20himself%20gazing%20with%20idle%20lust%20at%20one%20of%20the%20young%2C%20long-legged%20girls%20who%20pranced%20around%20town%20%E2%80%93%20their%20untethered%20breasts%20bouncing%20beneath%20the%20thinnest%20of%20cotton%20jerseys.%20But%20he%20never%20enjoyed%20the%20sensation%2C%20for%20it%20always%20made%20him%20wonder%20whether%20Ellen%20felt%20the%20same%20stirring%20when%20she%20looked%20at%20the%20tanned%2C%20slim%20young%20men%20who%20so%20perfectly%20complemented%20the%20long-legged%20girls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEllen%20is%20also%20much%20less%20sympathetic%20in%20the%20novel%20(though%20admittedly%20in%20the%20film%20she%E2%80%99s%20a%20cardboard%20cutout%20of%20virtuous%20motherhood%20and%20wifedom).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20moves%20around%20as%20a%20shell%20of%20a%20person%2C%20a%20terrible%20snob%20disappointed%20by%20her%20social%20status%20and%20too%20embarrassed%20and%20ashamed%20to%20do%20anything%20about%20it%2C%20%E2%80%9Ctortured%20by%20thoughts%20she%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20think%20%E2%80%93%20thoughts%20of%20chances%20missed%20and%20lives%20that%20could%20have%20been%E2%80%9D.%20Like%20Brody%2C%20she%20is%20drowning%20in%20self-loathing%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20made%20sure%20that%20everyone%20she%20met%20knew%20she%20had%20started%20her%20Amity%20life%20on%20an%20entirely%20different%20plane.%20She%20was%20aware%20of%20what%20she%20was%20doing%2C%20and%20she%20hated%20herself%20for%20it%2C%20because%20in%20fact%20she%20loved%20her%20husband%20deeply%2C%20adored%20her%20children%2C%20and%20%E2%80%93%20for%20most%20of%20the%20year%20%E2%80%93%20was%20quite%20content%20with%20her%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hooper%20of%20the%20novel%20is%20similarly%20transformed%20by%20the%20film%20from%20an%20arrogant%20show-off%2C%20vaingloriously%20pursuing%20fame%20as%20a%20scientist%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20everything%20else%2C%20into%20a%20smart%2C%20responsible%20and%20energetic%20ball%20of%20fun%2C%20fully%20embodied%20by%20dynamo%20actor%20Richard%20Dreyfuss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20Quint%20%E2%80%93%20the%20mythical%2C%20Ahab-esque%20hunter%20(%E2%80%9CBrody%20saw%20fever%20in%20Quint%E2%80%99s%20face%20%E2%80%93%20a%20heat%20that%20lit%20up%20his%20dark%20eyes%2C%20an%20intensity%20that%20drew%20his%20lips%20back%20from%20his%20teeth%20in%20a%20crooked%20smile%E2%80%9D)%20%E2%80%93%20remains%20fundamentally%20unchanged%2C%20even%20though%20his%20unyielding%20brutality%20seems%20more%20appealing%20in%20the%20novel%20than%20in%20the%20film%2C%20with%20Robert%20Shaw%20portraying%20him%20as%20an%20antisocial%20maniac.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20revision%20includes%20the%20whole%20dynamic%20of%20the%20Brody%20family.%20The%20delightful%20moments%20between%20the%20kids%20and%20their%20parents%2C%20reflecting%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20superpower%20as%20a%20director%20(his%20talent%20for%20bringing%20sentimental%20family%20moments%20to%20life)%2C%20are%20absent%20from%20the%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20something%20depressing%20about%20Brody%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20his%20family.%20He%20has%20virtually%20no%20interaction%20with%20his%20children%2C%20and%20when%20he%20does%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20like%20this%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20oldest%20boy%2C%20Billy%2C%20lay%20on%20the%20couch%2C%20leaning%20on%20an%20elbow.%20Martin%2C%20the%20middle%20son%2C%20age%20twelve%2C%20lounged%20in%20an%20easy%20chair%2C%20his%20shoeless%20feet%20propped%20up%20on%20the%20coffee%20table.%20Eight-year-old%20Sean%20sat%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20his%20back%20against%20the%20couch%2C%20stroking%20a%20cat%20in%20his%20lap.%20%E2%80%9CHow%20goes%20it%3F%E2%80%9D%20said%20Brody.%20%E2%80%9CGood%2C%20Dad%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Bill%2C%20without%20shifting%20his%20gaze%20from%20the%20television.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20%E2%80%98easy%20to%20swallow%E2%80%99%20better%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20populating%20a%20novel%20with%20unlikable%20characters%20and%20depressing%20family%20scenes%20is%20not%20a%20problem%20in%20and%20of%20itself.%20Popeye%20from%20William%20Faulkner%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguin.com.au%2Fbooks%2Fsanctuary-9780099541028%5C%22%3ESanctuary%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20hardly%20likeable%2C%20neither%20is%20pompous%20Nick%20Carraway%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguin.com.au%2Fbooks%2Fthe-great-gatsby-9781784877088%5C%22%3EThe%20Great%20Gatsby%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20and%20you%E2%80%99d%20be%20hard%20pressed%20to%20find%20a%20Dickens%20novel%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20feature%20some%20degree%20of%20family%20strife.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20Jaws%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Cman%20versus%20beast%E2%80%9D%20tale%2C%20a%20melodramatic%20thriller%2C%20it%20creates%20a%20flat%20feeling%3A%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20wholly%20mind%20the%20prospect%20of%20these%20characters%20being%20eaten%20by%20a%20shark.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Benchley%20%E2%80%93%20despite%20occasional%20flaws%20in%20the%20writing%20%E2%80%93%20does%20capture%20something%20of%20the%20dismal%20inconsistencies%20and%20banalities%20of%20being%20human.%20The%20complex%20self-loathing%20of%20the%20characters%20contrasts%20with%20the%20brutal%20and%20unthinking%20power%20%E2%80%93%20the%20genius%20for%20action%20and%20killing%20%E2%80%93%20of%20the%20shark.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FU1fu_sA7XhE%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cspan%3ESpielberg%20%E2%80%98buffed%20out%20the%20scratches%E2%80%99%20in%20Bentley%E2%80%99s%20novel%20for%20his%20film.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20redacts%20the%20frailties%20and%20faults%20of%20the%20characters%2C%20turning%20an%20adult%20(albeit%20imperfect)%20novel%20into%20family-friendly%20fodder.%20Spielberg%20took%20a%20low-key%20thriller%20doubling%20as%20a%20study%20of%20a%20small%20American%20community%20and%20turned%20it%20into%20the%20kind%20of%20blockbuster%20that%20would%20get%20people%20back%20into%20%E2%80%93%20and%20keep%20them%20in%20%E2%80%93%20cinemas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20comes%20as%20no%20surprise%20that%20the%20film%20also%20excises%20much%20of%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20pointed%20class%20critique.%20Note%2C%20for%20example%2C%20this%20description%20of%20the%20summer%20people%20early%20in%20the%20book%2C%20the%20haves%20to%20the%20local%20have-nots%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EPrivilege%20had%20been%20bred%20into%20them%20with%20genetic%20certainty.%20As%20their%20eyes%20were%20blue%20or%20brown%2C%20so%20their%20tastes%20and%20consciences%20were%20determined%20by%20other%20generations.%20They%20had%20no%20vitamin%20deficiencies%2C%20no%20sickle-cell%20anaemia.%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20Their%20bodies%20were%20lean%2C%20their%20muscles%20toned%20by%20boxing%20lessons%20at%20age%20nine%2C%20riding%20lessons%20at%20twelve%2C%20and%20tennis%20lessons%20ever%20since.%20They%20had%20no%20body%20odour.%20When%20they%20sweated%2C%20the%20girls%20smelled%20faintly%20of%20perfume%3B%20the%20boys%20smelled%20simply%20clean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20sure%2C%20would%20hold%20the%20novel%20up%20as%20an%20inferior%20work.%20At%20a%20technical%20level%2C%20they%E2%80%99d%20probably%20be%20right.%20But%20while%20it%E2%80%99s%20pretentious%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20also%20much%20more%20ambitious%20than%20the%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20something%20easy%20to%20swallow%20necessarily%20better%20for%20the%20digestion%3F%20Only%20a%20shark%20could%20answer%20that.%20The%20novel%20is%20ugly%20in%20places.%20But%20where%20it%20works%2C%20it%20works%20at%20the%20level%20of%20great%20literature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBenchley%E2%80%99s%20novel%20lingers%20longer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20outcomes%20of%20Jaws%20was%20at%20least%20a%20couple%20of%20generations%20of%20people%20who%2C%20if%20not%20exactly%20afraid%20to%20go%20back%20in%20the%20water%2C%20had%20a%20tendency%20to%20hum%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20theme%20to%20themselves%20when%20wading%20into%20the%20surf%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBenchley%2C%20horrified%20by%20the%20bad%20rap%20his%20novel%20gave%20sharks%2C%20would%20go%20on%20to%20become%20an%20ecological%20activist%20focused%20on%20shark%20protection.%20In%202015%2C%20a%20shark%20was%20named%20after%20him%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhakaimagazine.com%2Fnews%2Fmeet-new-ninja-lanternshark%2F%5C%22%3EEtmopterus%20benchleyi%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBenchley%E2%80%99s%20Jaws%20may%20not%20immediately%20grab%20one%20as%20easily%20as%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20certainly%20not%20as%20technically%20accomplished.%20Its%20position%20in%20American%20literature%20is%20minor%20compared%20to%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20in%20Hollywood%20cinema.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20%E2%80%93%20or%2C%20perhaps%2C%20because%20of%20%E2%80%93%20its%20flaws%2C%20the%20novel%20is%20worth%20reading%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20blockbuster%20has%20virtually%20decimated%20the%20middle%20of%20American%20cinema%2C%20churning%20out%20masses%20of%20pleasurably%20forgettable%2C%20interchangeable%20films%20that%20float%20like%20a%20thick%20slick%20of%20chum%20on%20the%20water%E2%80%99s%20surface.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F218519%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fari-mattes-97857%5C%22%3EAri%20Mattes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lecturer%20in%20Communications%20and%20Media%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-notre-dame-australia-852%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Notre%20Dame%20Australia%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fjaws-turns-50-reading-peter-benchleys-novel-you-barely-mind-if-its-self-loathing-characters-are-eaten-by-a-genius-shark-218519%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3