livemint.com%2Fcompanies%2Fstart-ups%2Findian-startup-funding-shrinks-by-73-in-2023-what-models-companies-can-adopt-now-11702277047353.html%5C%22%3EMint%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%2C%20citing%20data%20from%20research%20platform%20Tracxn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20seven-year%20low%20in%20India%20funding%20is%20not%20something%20specific%20to%20India%20but%20seen%20across%20the%20major%20geographies%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20China%20and%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20as%20well%20as%20globally%2C%20(with)%20similar%20lows%20in%20funding%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Ftech%2Ffunding%2Ffunding-in-indian-startups-sinks-to-its-lowest-since-2017%2Farticleshow%2F105848729.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20Neha%20Singh%2C%20cofounder%20of%20Tracxn%2C%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EIndian%20startups%20witnessed%20a%20nearly%2073%25%20decline%20in%20fundraising%20in%202023%2C%20raising%20%247%20billion%20as%20compared%20to%20%2425%20billion%20in%20the%20previous%20year%20%E2%80%93%20a%20significant%20drop%20from%20the%20funding%20recorded%20in%202022%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20funded%20sectors%20included%20fintech%2C%20retail%2C%20enterprise%20applications%2C%20environment%20tech%2C%20and%20space%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20fintech%20sector%20has%20received%20%242.1%20billion%20in%20funding%20as%20compared%20to%20%245.8B%20received%20in%20the%20same%20period%20last%20year.%20PhonePe%20was%20the%20top%20funded%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20retail%20sector%20received%20a%20total%20of%20%241.9%20billion%20in%20funding%20in%202023%2C%20a%2067%25%20decline%20from%202022.%20Lenskart%20was%20the%20top%20funded%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Tracxn%20report%2C%20India%20dropped%20to%20the%20fifth%20position%20in%202023%20among%20the%20highest-funded%20geographies%20globally.%20It%20had%20been%20ranked%20fourth%20in%20both%202022%20and%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20mature%20startups%20have%20been%20the%20most%20affected%20by%20the%20slowdown%2C%20as%20big-ticket%20investors%20such%20as%20Tiger%20Global%20and%20SoftBank%2C%20known%20for%20their%20aggressive%20deal-making%2C%20took%20a%20backseat.%20%E2%80%9CInvestors%20also%20took%20longer%20to%20write%20new%20cheques%2C%20turning%20cautious%20after%20questions%20were%20raised%20over%20corporate%20governance%20at%20several%20venture-backed%20startups%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704448815000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05134407%2Fimage-1686.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Ffunding-for-indian-startups-hit-a-seven-year-low-in-the-december-quarter-of-2023-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Indian%20startups%20witnessed%20a%20nearly%2073%25%20decline%20in%20fundraising%20in%202023%2C%20raising%20%247%20billion%20as%20compared%20to%20%2425%20billion%20in%20the%20previous%20year%20%E2%80%93%20a%20significant%20drop%20from%20the%20funding%20recorded%20in%202022.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Ffunding-for-indian-startups-hit-a-seven-year-low-in-the-december-quarter-of-2023-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CBI%20to%20Probe%20Delhi%20Mohalla%20Clinics%20Over%20'Fake'%20Medical%20Tests%2C%20Corruption%20Allegations%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05152523%2FEffect-57.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Union%20home%20ministry%20has%20directed%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20to%20probe%20into%20the%20alleged%20scam%20in%20the%20Delhi%20government%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20programme%20of%20Mohalla%20Clinics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20lieutenant%20governor%2C%20V.K.%20Saxena%2C%20just%20a%20day%20earlier%20had%20recommended%20that%20CBI%20launch%20an%20investigation%20into%20the%20running%20of%20Mohalla%20Clinics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party-led%20Delhi%20government%20has%20been%20offering%20450%20medical%20tests%20free%20of%20cost%20to%20poor%20patients%20through%20its%20Mohalla%20Clinics%20initiative%20from%20January%201%2C%202023.%20Two%20private%20companies%20have%20been%20entrusted%20with%20the%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20allegations%20of%20fake%20tests%20and%20dummy%20patients.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CData%20clearly%20revealed%20that%20fake%20lab%20tests%20were%20carried%20out%20at%20these%20mohalla%20clinics%20that%20need%20to%20be%20further%20inquired%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20official%20from%20the%20L-G%E2%80%99s%20office%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fdelhi%2Fhome-ministry-cbi-probe-delhi-mohalla-clinics-9096236%2F%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Saxena%E2%80%99s%20office%2C%20several%20disingenuous%20methods%20are%20being%20employed%20by%20the%20staff%20of%20Mohalla%20Clinics%20to%20get%20%E2%80%9Clakhs%20of%20tests%20conducted%20on%20dummy%20patients%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20government%20money%20is%20paid%20to%20private%20firms%20as%20per%20an%20inquiry%20by%20the%20Vigilance%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaxena%E2%80%99s%20office%20said%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20only%20the%20digit%20%E2%80%9C0%E2%80%9D%20was%20entered%20in%20the%20section%20meant%20for%20mobile%20numbers%20in%2011%2C657%20cases%3B%20the%20space%20was%20left%20blank%20in%208%2C251%20cases%3B%20mobile%20numbers%20of%203%2C092%20patients%20were%20entered%20as%209999999999%3B%20400%20mobile%20numbers%20began%20with%201%2C2%2C3%2C4%20or%205%3B%20and%20the%20same%20number%20was%20used%20more%20than%2015%20times%20in%20around%20a%20thousand%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20the%20Vigilance%20department%20report%2C%20Saxena%E2%80%99s%20office%20said%20as%20many%20as%2020%2C000%20tests%20were%20recommended%20by%20the%20outsourced%20labs%20either%20on%20blank%20mobile%20numbers%20or%20on%20%E2%80%9C0%E2%80%9D%20digit.%20According%20to%20LG%E2%80%99s%20office%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cscam%E2%80%9D%20runs%20into%20hundreds%20of%20crores.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20alleged%20scam%20first%20became%20public%20in%20September%20last%20year%20after%20it%20emerged%20that%20some%20doctors%20and%20staff%20of%20seven%20Mohalla%20Clinics%20in%20Southwest%2C%20Shahdara%2C%20and%20Northeast%20districts%20were%20employing%20dubious%20means%20to%20mark%20their%20attendance%20through%20pre-recorded%20videos.%20Those%20doctors%20were%20later%20removed%20from%20the%20empanelment%20of%20doctors%20and%20a%20case%20was%20registered%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Delhi%20health%20minister%20Saurabh%20Bharadwaj%20said%20he%20had%20received%20complaints%20against%20a%20few%20doctors%20coming%20late%20or%20leaving%20early%20from%20work.%20He%20had%20ordered%20action%20against%20them%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704448700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05152523%2FEffect-57.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcbi-to-probe-delhi-mohalla-clinics-over-fake-medical-tests-corruption-allegations%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Union%20home%20ministry%20ordered%20the%20probe%20a%20day%20after%20Delhi%20LG%20recommended%20an%20investigation%20into%20the%20matter%2C%20accusing%20authorities%20of%20using%20disingenuous%20methods%20to%20get%20'lakhs%20of%20tests%20conducted%20on%20dummy%20patients'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcbi-to-probe-delhi-mohalla-clinics-over-fake-medical-tests-corruption-allegations%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20We%20Know%20About%20India's%20Post-Covid%20Economy%20Recovery%20and%20Rising%20Inequality%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05124611%2Fandrea-leopardi-B4qmgZdSQp0-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20part%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98s%20%E2%80%98India%20Black%20Boxed%E2%80%99%20series.%20Read%20it%20here%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fintroducing-india-black-boxed%5C%22%3EIntroduction%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-do-we-really-know-about-indias-gdp%5C%22%3EPart%20I%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20largest%20luxury%20and%20premium%20watch%20retailer%2C%20Ethos%2C%20which%20sells%20Omega%2C%20Jaeger%20LeCoultre%2C%20Panerai%2C%20Bvlgari%2C%20Longines%2C%20Baume%20%26amp%3B%20Mercier%2C%20Tissot%2C%20Raymond%20Weil%2C%20etc.%2C%20each%20of%20them%20costing%20lakhs%2C%20reported%20a%2044%25%20increase%20in%20sales%20and%20262%25%20rise%20in%20net%20profit%20in%20the%20March%20quarter%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%20%3C%2Fem%3Erecently%20reported.%20Similarly%2C%20while%20underwear%20sales%20have%20collapsed%20and%20two-wheeler%20sales%20have%20crashed%20to%20the%202012%20levels%2C%20BMW%20has%20reported%2037%25%20higher%20sales%20for%20its%20luxury%20cars%20in%202022.%20The%20World%20Inequality%20Report%202022%20had%20called%20India%20%E2%80%98a%20poor%20and%20very%20unequal%20country%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESUV%20sales%20in%20India%20are%20rising%20while%20sales%20of%20entry%20level%20cars%20and%20two-wheelers%20are%20shrinking%20or%20lower%20than%20pre-Covid%20times%3B%20should%20recent%20statistics%20like%20this%20surprise%20us%2C%20still%3F%20While%20the%20government%20would%20like%20India%E2%80%99s%20citizens%20to%20believe%20that%20India%20came%20out%20of%20the%20Covid%20exogenous%20shock%20in%20a%20V-shaped%20recovery%2C%20and%20has%20become%20the%20fastest%20growing%20large%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20most%20economists%20outside%20of%20government%20have%20repeatedly%20argued%20what%20India%20experienced%20has%20been%20a%20K-shaped%20rebound%20(not%20recovery).%20Could%20these%20kinds%20of%20data%20be%20behind%20the%20fact%20that%20suddenly%20India%20became%20the%20fifth%C2%A0largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20overtaking%20the%20UK%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20300px)%2085vw%2C%20300px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism-150x150.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691446%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20many%20dimensions%20to%20this%20K-shaped%20recovery.%20First%2C%20the%20stock%20market%20continued%20to%20boom%20through%20much%20of%20Covid%2C%20while%20the%20real%20economy%20was%20tanking%2C%20clearly%20benefitting%20the%20minuscule%20minority%20who%20benefit%20from%20investing%20in%20stocks%20and%20bonds.%20A%20second%20dimension%20of%20the%20K-shaped%20recovery%20was%20that%20listed%20company%20profits%20rose%20to%20a%20seven-year%20high%2C%20real%20wages%20shrank%20and%20jobs%20shrank.%20A%20third%20dimension%20was%20that%20the%20organised%2C%20formal%20sectors%20of%20the%20economy%20generally%20performed%20well%2C%20despite%20the%20shock%2C%20except%20for%20a%20limited%20period%20of%20time%2C%20while%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20was%20already%20reeling%20from%20consecutive%20shocks%20inflicted%20by%20the%20government%20by%20one%20policy%20mistake%20after%20another%20(demonetisation%2C%20badly%20planned%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20in%20July%202017%2C%20and%20then%20a%20lockdown%20of%20the%20entire%20economy%20and%20workforce%20at%20four%20hours%20notice%20in%20March%202020%20when%20there%20were%20less%20than%20600%20Covid%20cases%2C%20needlessly%20strict%20and%20national%20in%20scope).%20The%20unorganised%20and%20MSME%20sectors%20have%20barely%20recovered%20from%20the%20multiple%20shocks%20in%20succession%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20why%20joblessness%20remains%20at%20a%2050-year%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20fourth%20dimension%20of%20the%20K-shaped%20recovery%20was%20the%20less%20well%20known%20facet%20that%2045%20million%20joined%20agriculture%20in%202020%2C%20and%20an%20additional%20seven%20million%20were%20added%20to%20the%20farm%20workforce%20in%202021%2C%20during%20the%20first%20and%20second%20wave%20reverse%20migrations.%20Even%20in%202022%20(according%20to%20the%20latest%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%202021-22)%2C%20the%20absolute%20number%20of%20workers%20in%20agriculture%20has%20not%20fallen.%20These%20increases%20in%20farm%20workforce%20totally%20reversed%20a%2015-year%20trend%2C%20which%20saw%20an%20absolute%20decline%20in%20farm%20workforce%20since%202004%2C%20a%20first%20in%20post%20independence%20history).%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20manufacturing%20employment%20has%20not%20risen%2C%20and%20has%20stagnated.%20So%20the%20entire%20process%20of%20structural%20change%20that%20had%20gathered%20momentum%20between%202004%20and%202014%2C%20when%20the%20economy%20grew%20at%208%25%20per%20year%2C%20an%20unprecedented%20phenomenon%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20post%20independence%20history%2C%20has%20not%20only%20been%20stalled%2C%20it%20has%20aborted%20and%20been%20reversed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22What%20Do%20We%20Really%20Know%20About%20India's%20GDP%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-do-we-really-know-about-indias-gdp%5C%22%3EWhat%20Do%20We%20Really%20Know%20About%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20joblessness%20rose%2C%20consumption%20demand%20has%20fallen%20or%20stagnated.%20In%20FY%202022-23%2C%20the%20Second%20Advance%20Estimates%20for%20GDP%20released%20February%202023%20suggest%20that%20per%20capita%20consumption%2C%20on%20average%2C%20has%20risen%20slightly%20above%20the%202019%20level.%20Inevitably%2C%20with%20incomes%20stagnant%2C%20the%20household%20savings%20to%20GDP%20ratio%20has%20fallen%20in%20recent%20years%3B%20people%20are%20maintaining%20consumption%20by%20dissaving.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20were%20plenty%20in%20the%20top%20end%20of%20the%20middle%20class%20and%20the%20upper%20classes%20who%2C%20during%20Covid%2C%20were%20not%20eating%20out%2C%20not%20travelling%2C%20not%20going%20on%20holidays%20in%20India%20or%20abroad%2C%20and%20hence%20were%20saving%20more%2C%20and%20could%20now%20splurge%20on%20SUVs%20or%20more%20expensive%20cars.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20population%2C%20seriously%20impacted%20by%20joblessness%2C%20stagnant%20wages%20and%20consistently%20high%20inflation%2C%20fuelled%20by%20government%20taxes%20on%20petrol%2C%20diesel%20and%20cooking%20gas%2C%20which%20are%20inputs%20into%20both%20production%20of%20goods%20and%20services%2C%20has%20less%20disposable%20income%20left%20over%20to%20buy%20such%20luxuries%20as%20motor%20vehicles%2C%20whether%20two%20wheelers%20or%20small%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EViral%20Acharya%2C%20former%20deputy%20governor%20of%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20NYU%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20academic%20paper%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20five%20firms%E2%80%99%20share%20in%20total%20assets%20of%20the%20non-financial%20sectors%20rose%20from%2010%25%20in%201991%20to%20nearly%2018%25%20in%202021%2C%20whereas%20the%20share%20of%20the%20next%20Big%205%20business%20groups%20fell%20from%2018%25%20in%201992%20to%20less%20than%209%25.%20This%20growth%20has%20been%20biggest%20in%20the%20last%20decade.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20other%20words%2C%20Big%205%20grew%20not%20just%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20smallest%20firms%2C%20but%20also%20of%20the%20next%20largest%20firms%2C%E2%80%9D%20Acharya%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Big%205%20industrial%20groups%20referred%20to%20in%20the%20paper%20are%20the%20Mukesh%20Ambani-helmed%20Reliance%20Group%2C%20Tata%20Group%2C%20Aditya%20Birla%20Group%2C%20Adani%20Group%20and%20Bharti%20Telecom.%20He%20said%20the%20growth%20of%20such%20conglomerates%20raises%20several%20concerns%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%20risk%20of%20crony%20capitalism%2C%20related%20party%20transactions%20within%20their%20byzantine%20corporate%20organisation%20charts%2C%20and%20over-leveraging%20due%20to%20an%20implicit%20too-big-to-fail%20perception%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESantosh%20Mehrotra%20is%20Professorial%20Fellow%2C%20Nehru%20Memorial%20Museum%20and%20Library%2C%20New%20Delhi%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704447018000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05124611%2Fandrea-leopardi-B4qmgZdSQp0-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-we-know-about-indias-post-covid-economy-recovery-and-rising-inequality%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20upper%20and%20upper%20middle%20classes%20saved%20money%20during%20the%20pandemic%20that%20they%20are%20spending%20on%20luxury%20goods%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20population%20has%20been%20seriously%20impacted%20by%20joblessness%2C%20stagnant%20wages%20and%20consistently%20high%20inflation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-we-know-about-indias-post-covid-economy-recovery-and-rising-inequality%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20New%20Year%E2%80%99s%20Prayer%20for%20Jimmy%20Lai%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05134056%2FJimmy_Lai_go_to_The_Court_of_Final_Appeal_20201231.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ESeeing%20Jimmy%20Lai%20in%20shackles%20entering%20a%20Hong%20Kong%20courtroom%20this%20week%20was%20a%20shock%20for%20me%20on%20a%20personal%20level.%20I%E2%80%99d%20gotten%20to%20know%20the%20Hong%20Kong%20media%20mogul%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20pro-democracy%20newspaper%20%3Cem%3EApple%20Daily%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20late%201990s%20when%20I%20worked%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20Hong%20Kong%20bureau.%20He%20was%2C%20pardon%20the%20clich%C3%A9%2C%20larger%20than%20life%20%E2%80%93%20a%20bear%20of%20a%20man%20with%20a%20gentle%20spirit%20whose%20passion%20for%20democracy%20was%20equaled%20only%20by%20his%20commitment%20to%20freedom%20of%20expression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20a%20self-made%20man%2C%20unlike%20many%20mainland%20millionaires%20who%20owe%20their%20fortunes%20to%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20connections.%20At%20the%20age%20of%2012%2C%20Jimmy%20stowed%20away%20on%20a%20ship%20headed%20from%20the%20mainland%20to%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20went%20to%20work%20in%20the%20garment%20industry.%20A%20brilliant%20apprentice%2C%20he%20moved%20up%20the%20ranks%2C%20became%20a%20manager%2C%20owner%2C%20and%20eventually%20the%20CEO%20and%20president%20of%20a%20multinational%20clothing%20and%20retail%20empire%2C%20Giordano%2C%20which%20at%20its%20peak%20had%20outlets%20across%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJimmy%20eventually%20sold%20off%20most%20of%20his%20garment%20and%20retail%20interests%20to%20launch%20media%20outlets%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3ENext%20Magazine%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%201990%20and%20the%20hugely%20popular%20%3Cem%3EApple%20Daily%3C%2Fem%3E%20newspaper%20in%201995%2C%20both%20of%20which%20had%20a%20hard-hitting%20reporting%20and%20editorial%20style%20that%20championed%20democracy%20and%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20afraid%20to%20take%20on%20Beijing%20or%20those%20who%20kowtowed%20to%20the%20CCP%20in%20the%20Hong%20Kong%20political%20and%20business%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20it%20was%20at%20his%20home%20or%20a%20favourite%20Hong%20Kong%20restaurant%2C%20whenever%20we%20met%20there%20was%20usually%20a%20meal%20involved%20%E2%80%93%20and%20his%20appetite%20for%20good%20food%20and%20drink%20was%20nearly%20as%20voracious%20as%20his%20appetite%20for%20conversation%20and%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20first%20met%20Jimmy%20in%201998%2C%20the%20year%20after%20Hong%20Kong%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Chandover%E2%80%9D%20from%20Britain%20to%20Beijing%2C%20and%20our%20meetings%20%E2%80%93%20often%20with%20other%20members%20of%20the%20press%2C%20academics%2C%20local%20politicians%2C%20and%20human-rights%20activists%20%E2%80%93%20would%20inevitably%20turn%20to%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20mainland%20was%20undermining%20its%20%E2%80%9Cone%20country%2C%20two%20systems%E2%80%9D%20promise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20devout%20Catholic%2C%20Jimmy%E2%80%99s%20faith%20was%20%E2%80%93%20and%20is%20%E2%80%93%20central%20to%20his%20identity%2C%20and%20we%20were%20frequently%20joined%20by%20local%20clergy%20around%20a%20big%20table%2C%20where%20Jimmy%2C%20while%20generously%20listening%20to%20all%20present%2C%20held%20court.%20His%20stories%2C%20often%20filled%20with%20outrage%20over%20injustices%20done%20to%20the%20Hong%20Kong%20people%2C%20ranged%20from%20the%20Japanese%20occupation%20during%20World%20War%20II%20to%20the%20riots%20against%20British%20colonial%20rule%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20and%20the%20threat%20to%20judicial%20independence%20after%201997.%20But%20they%20were%20also%20filled%20with%20goodwill%2C%20humour%2C%20and%20Jimmy%E2%80%99s%20bedrock%20belief%20that%20we%2C%20as%20his%20faith%20teaches%2C%20should%20%E2%80%9CDo%20unto%20others%20as%20we%20would%20have%20them%20do%20unto%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20I%20looked%20up%20to%20Jimmy.%20He%20was%20to%20me%20%E2%80%93%20a%20young%20journalist%20on%20my%20first%20real%20overseas%20assignment%20%E2%80%93%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20freedoms%20that%20the%20great%20majority%20of%20Hong%20Kongers%20cherished%2C%20and%20an%20example%20of%20why%20the%20%E2%80%9Cone%20country%2C%20two%20systems%E2%80%9D%20promise%20made%20by%20Beijing%20in%201997%20was%20so%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20promise%20was%20supposed%20to%20last%20at%20least%2050%20years%2C%20until%202047%2C%20over%20which%20time%20Hong%20Kong%20would%20gradually%20expand%20its%20citizens%E2%80%99democratic%20rights.%20Sadly%2C%20that%20promise%20was%20shattered%2C%20along%20with%20the%20lives%20of%20Jimmy%20Lai%20and%20thousands%20of%20other%20lesser-known%20activists%2C%20in%20a%20brutal%20crackdown%20by%20craven%20Hong%20Kong%20authorities%20under%20the%20sway%20of%20Communist%20Party%20leaders%20in%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVisibly%20thinner%20and%20fatigued%20after%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20days%20behind%20bars%2C%20Jimmy%2C%20who%20turned%2076%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20is%20currently%20imprisoned%20in%20a%20maximum-security%20cell%20under%20bogus%20%E2%80%9Cfraud%E2%80%9D%20charges.%20He%20now%20faces%20life%20in%20prison%20on%20equally%20ludicrous%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20security%E2%80%9D%20charges%20of%20publishing%20%E2%80%9Cseditious%20materials%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20any%20honest%20individual%20knows%2C%20it%20is%20not%20Jimmy%20Lai%20but%20those%20who%20do%20the%20bidding%20of%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20in%20Beijing%20that%20are%20the%20true%20threats%20to%20Hong%20Kongers%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20security%E2%80%9D%20and%20way%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Mark%20Clifford%2C%20award-winning%20journalist%20and%20president%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thecfhk.org%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Committee%20for%20Freedom%20in%20Hong%20Kong%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20me%20this%20week%2C%20instead%20of%20living%20up%20to%20the%20promise%20of%20one%20country%2C%20two%20systems%2C%20%E2%80%9CChina%E2%80%99s%20Xi%20Jinping%20demands%20total%20submission.%20Even%20one%20person%20sticking%20up%20is%20like%20a%20nail%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20hammered%20down.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COf%20course%2C%E2%80%9D%20Clifford%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CJimmy%20is%20not%20your%20average%20nail.%20His%20advocacy%20on%20behalf%20of%20freedom%2C%20his%20advocacy%20for%20the%20democracy%20that%20China%20promised%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20is%20an%20unambiguous%20challenge%20to%20a%20communist%20dictatorship.%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20matter%20that%20Jimmy%20is%20a%2076-year-old%20man%20who%20has%20always%20preached%20nonviolence.%20He%20dares%20to%20challenge%20Beijing%20through%20his%20commitment%20to%20truth%20and%20by%20having%20strong%20moral%20values%20that%20he%20has%20the%20courage%20to%20live%20and%2C%20if%20necessary%2C%20die%20by.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESebastien%20Lai%2C%20Jimmy%E2%80%99s%20son%2C%20who%20was%20just%20a%20young%20boy%20the%20last%20time%20I%20met%20him%2C%20is%20heading%20the%20international%20campaign%20to%20free%20his%20father%2C%20tirelessly%20meeting%20with%20legislators%2C%20human-rights%20organisations%2C%20and%20heads%20of%20state%20around%20the%20globe.%20Writing%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Globe%20and%20Mail%3C%2Fem%3E%20this%20week%2C%20Sebastien%2C%20now%2028%2C%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%202020%2C%20the%20Hong%20Kong%20government%20accused%20my%20father%2C%20Jimmy%20Lai%2C%20of%20charges%20under%20China%E2%80%99s%20national%20security%20law%2C%20including%20%E2%80%9Ccolluding%20with%20foreign%20forces%E2%80%9D%20and%20sedition.%20The%20truth%20is%20much%20less%20convoluted.%20For%20almost%20three%20decades%2C%20my%20father%20published%20Apple%20Daily%2C%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20largest%20pro-democracy%20newspaper%2C%20and%20was%20one%20of%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20most%20outspoken%20and%20dauntless%20critics.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFor%20this%2C%20the%20authorities%20are%20putting%20on%20an%20elaborate%20show%20to%20discredit%20and%20silence%20him.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOn%20Monday%20morning%2C%20when%20his%20sham%20trial%20finally%20began%20after%20more%20than%201%2C000%20days%20of%20pre-trial%20detention%2C%20sniffer%20dogs%20patrolled%20the%20street%20outside%20of%20West%20Kowloon%20Court%2C%20and%20police%20officers%20deployed%20to%20secure%20the%20area%E2%80%941%2C000%20of%20them%2C%20according%20to%20reports%E2%80%94scanned%20passing%20cars%20for%20bombs.%20Law%20enforcement%20dwarfed%20both%20press%20presence%20and%20the%20crowd%20queueing%20to%20witness%20the%20trial.%20Local%20media%20have%20reported%20that%20the%20same%20show%20of%20force%20will%20be%20deployed%20every%20day%20for%20the%20duration%20of%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%2080-day%20trial.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20tight%20security%2C%20like%20the%20trial%20itself%2C%20is%20a%20co-ordinated%20performance%20to%20paint%20him%20as%20a%20dangerous%20man.%20But%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20it%20betrays%20something%20else%3A%20how%20terrified%20tyranny%20is%20of%20defiance%2C%20and%20how%20insecure%20Beijing%20and%20its%20puppets%20are%20in%20the%20face%20of%20a%20man%20who%20stands%20up%20for%20freedom%20and%20speaks%20truth%20to%20power%2C%20whatever%20the%20cost%20may%20be.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%E2%80%99m%20not%20sure%20how%20much%20access%20Jimmy%20has%20to%20the%20outside%20world%2C%20but%20I%E2%80%99m%20sure%20of%20one%20thing%3A%20He%E2%80%99s%20proud%20of%20his%20boy%2C%20Sebastien%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20the%20outcome%20of%20his%20sham%20of%20a%20trial.%20The%20irony%20is%20almost%20too%20painful.%20In%20a%20Kafkaesque%20nightmare%2C%20a%20man%20who%20believes%20in%20truth%20and%20justice%20finds%20himself%20in%20a%20predetermined%20trial%20that%20respects%20neither.%20Yet%2C%20unlike%20Kafka%E2%80%99s%20Josef%20K%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Trial%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Jimmy%2C%20like%20Socrates%2C%20has%20lived%20a%20fully%20examined%20life%2C%20guided%20by%20faith%20not%20fear%2C%20truth%20not%20deception.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Clifford%2C%20a%20longtime%20friend%20and%20colleague%20of%20Jimmy%E2%80%99s%2C%20explained%20in%20my%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmichaeljudge.substack.com%2Fp%2Fthe-tragedy-of-hong-kong-and-why%3Fs%3Dw%5C%22%3E%C2%A0TFP%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0with%20him%20last%20year%20upon%20the%20release%20of%20his%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FToday-Hong-Kong-Tomorrow-World%2Fdp%2F1250279178%3Fasc_source%3D01GTER1X19F274KT48MCTDGTQG%26tag%3Dnamespacebran383-20%5C%22%3EToday%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20Tomorrow%20the%20World%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20Communist%20leaders%20%E2%80%9Ccrave%20legitimacy%2C%20but%20they%20fear%20their%20own%20people.%20And%20they%20know%20that%20despite%20all%20the%20material%20progress%2C%20building%20the%20second-largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20et%20cetera%2C%20their%20people%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20freedom.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20Jimmy%20Lai%E2%80%99s%20sense%20of%20certainty%20in%20his%20cause%20%E2%80%93%20buoyed%20by%20his%20love%20for%20his%20wife%2C%20Teresa%2C%20his%20children%2C%20and%20his%20Catholic%20faith%20%E2%80%93%20continues%20to%20flourish%2C%20even%20behind%20bars.%20As%20I%20wrote%20in%20my%20interview%20with%20Clifford%2C%20perhaps%20the%20most%20stirring%20words%20in%20his%20book%20%E2%80%93%20itself%20a%20moving%20testament%20to%20the%20character%20and%20endurance%20of%20Hong%20Kong%E2%80%99s%20democracy%20activists%20%E2%80%93%20weren%E2%80%99t%20written%20by%20the%20author%20but%20by%20Jimmy%2C%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20his%20old%20friend%20and%20fellow%20newspaperman%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EI%E2%80%99m%20adjusting%20very%20well%20in%20prison.%20Without%20the%20distraction%20of%20the%20world%20I%20can%20concentrate%20on%20reading%20my%20books%2C%20especially%20books%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20understand%20%5Bbefore%5D%2C%20I%20can%20understand%20now.%20It%E2%80%99s%20such%20a%20joy.%20My%20family%2C%20colleagues%2C%20and%20friends%20and%20even%20people%20here%20have%20been%20very%20supportive.%20I%20know%20I%20must%20have%20done%20the%20right%20thing.%20The%20Lord%20has%20rewarded%20me%20with%20sweet%20joy%20and%20love.%20%E2%80%A6%20I%20used%20to%20think%20I%20love%5Bd%5D%20freedom%20the%20most.%20Now%20I%20know%20I%20love%20Teresa%20the%20most.%20I%E2%80%99m%20a%20lucky%20man.%20My%20life%20has%20been%20so%20wonderful.%20I%20can%20face%20whatever%20suffering%20%5Bis%5D%20coming%20forth%20on%20me.%20%E2%80%A6%20Yes%2C%20I%E2%80%99ve%20enemies.%20But%20funny%20enough%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20bit%20of%20hate%2C%20not%20even%20a%20tiny%20bit.%20I%20tell%20myself%20if%20I%20can%20pray%20for%20my%20enemies%20and%20wish%20them%20well%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20have%20no%20fear.%20I%20really%20have%20no%20fear.%20I%20believe%20at%20the%20end%20righteousness%20and%20justice%20will%20prevail.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20New%20Year%2C%20I%20pray%20Jimmy%20is%20right.%20I%20also%20pray%20that%20I%2C%20and%20all%20those%20who%20know%20him%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20his%20family%20and%20loved%20ones%20%E2%80%93%20find%20strength%20in%20the%20courage%20of%20his%20convictions%2C%20and%20peace%20in%20the%20example%20of%20his%20compassion.%20But%20most%20of%20all%20I%20pray%20for%20my%20friend%2C%20that%20he%20may%20return%20to%20the%20loving%20arms%20of%20his%20Teresa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMichael%20Judge%2C%20a%20former%20deputy%20features%20editor%20at%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3Cem%3E%2C%20is%20a%20US-based%20poet%20and%20freelance%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmich